        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 8 at 9:32PM EDT by NWS Upton NY</headline>
        <description>At 932 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms over Westport, or near Norwalk, moving northeast at 25
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Bridgeport, Stamford, Norwalk, Milford, Shelton, New Canaan, Newtown,
Fairfield, Stratford, Trumbull, Westport, Ridgefield, Darien, Monroe,
and Wilton.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
